35 call sequence
36
37 u8g2_SetupBuffer_XYZ
38 u8x8_Setup_XYZ
39 u8x8_SetupDefaults(u8g2);
40 assign u8x8 callbacks
41 u8x8->display_cb(u8x8, U8X8_MSG_DISPLAY_SETUP_MEMORY, 0, NULL);
42 setup tile buffer
43
44
45 Arduino Uno Text Example
46> FONT_ROTATION INTERSECTION CLIPPING text data bss dec hex
47> 8700
48> x x x 7450 104 1116 8670 21de
49> - x x 7132 104 1115 8351 209f
50> x - x 7230 104 1116 8450 2102
51> - - x 7010 104 1115 8229 2025
52> - - - 6880 104 1115 8099 1fa3
53
54

63/*
64 The following macro enables 16 Bit mode.
65 Without defining this macro all calculations are done with 8 Bit (1 Byte) variables.
66 Especially on AVR architecture, this will save some space.
67 If this macro is defined, then U8g2 will switch to 16 Bit mode.
68 Use 16 Bit mode for any display with more than 240 pixel in one
69 direction.
70*/
71#define U8G2_16BIT
72
73
74/* always enable U8G2_16BIT on 32bit environments, see issue https://github.com/olikraus/u8g2/issues/1222 */
75#ifndef U8G2_16BIT
76#if defined(unix) || defined(__unix__) || defined(__arm__) || defined(__xtensa__) || defined(xtensa) || defined(__arc__) || defined(ESP8266) || defined(ESP_PLATFORM) || defined(__LUATOS__)
77#define U8G2_16BIT
78#endif
79#endif
80
81/*
82 The following macro switches the library into dynamic display buffer allocation mode.
83 Defining this constant will disable all static memory allocation for device memory buffer and thus allows the user to allocate device buffers statically.
84 Before using any display functions, the dynamic buffer *must* be assigned to the u8g2 struct using the u8g2_SetBufferPtr function.
85 When using dynamic allocation, the stack size must be increased by u8g2_GetBufferSize bytes.
86 */
87//#define U8G2_USE_DYNAMIC_ALLOC
88
89/* U8g2 feature selection, see also https://github.com/olikraus/u8g2/wiki/u8g2optimization */
90
91/*
92 The following macro enables the HVLine speed optimization.
93 It will consume about 40 bytes more in flash memory of the AVR.
94 HVLine procedures are also used by the text drawing functions.
95*/
96#ifndef U8G2_WITHOUT_HVLINE_SPEED_OPTIMIZATION
97#define U8G2_WITH_HVLINE_SPEED_OPTIMIZATION
98#endif
99
100/*
101 The following macro activates the early intersection check with the current visible area.
102 Clipping (and low level intersection calculation) will still happen and is controlled by U8G2_WITH_CLIPPING.
103 This early intersection check only improves speed for the picture loop (u8g2_FirstPage/NextPage).
104 With a full framebuffer in RAM and if most graphical elements are drawn within the visible area, then this
105 macro can be commented to reduce code size.
106*/
107#ifndef U8G2_WITHOUT_INTERSECTION
108#define U8G2_WITH_INTERSECTION
109#endif
110
111
112/*
113 Enable clip window support:
114 void u8g2_SetMaxClipWindow(u8g2_t *u8g2)
115 void u8g2_SetClipWindow(u8g2_t *u8g2, u8g2_uint_t clip_x0, u8g2_uint_t clip_y0, u8g2_uint_t clip_x1, u8g2_uint_t clip_y1 )
116 Setting a clip window will restrict all drawing to this window.
117 Clip window support requires about 200 bytes flash memory on AVR systems
118*/
119#ifndef U8G2_WITHOUT_CLIP_WINDOW_SUPPORT
120#define U8G2_WITH_CLIP_WINDOW_SUPPORT
121#endif
122
123/*
124 The following macro enables all four drawing directions for glyphs and strings.
125 If this macro is not defined, than a string can be drawn only in horizontal direction.
126
127 Jan 2020: Disabling this macro will save up to 600 bytes on AVR
128*/
129#ifndef U8G2_WITHOUT_FONT_ROTATION
130#define U8G2_WITH_FONT_ROTATION
131#endif
132
133/*
134 U8glib V2 contains support for unicode plane 0 (Basic Multilingual Plane, BMP).
135 The following macro activates this support. Deactivation would save some ROM.
136 This definition also defines the behavior of the expected string encoding.
137 If the following macro is defined, then the DrawUTF8 function is enabled and
138 the string argument for this function is assumed
139 to be UTF-8 encoded.
140 If the following macro is not defined, then all strings in the c-code are assumed
141 to be ISO 8859-1/CP1252 encoded.
142 Independently from this macro, the Arduino print function never accepts UTF-8
143 strings.
144
145 This macro does not affect the u8x8 string draw function.
146 u8x8 has also two function, one for pure strings and one for UTF8
147
148 Conclusion:
149 U8G2_WITH_UNICODE defined
150 - C-Code Strings must be UTF-8 encoded
151 - Full support of all 65536 glyphs of the unicode basic multilingual plane
152 - Up to 65536 glyphs of the font file can be used.
153 U8G2_WITH_UNICODE not defined
154 - C-Code Strings are assumbed to be ISO 8859-1/CP1252 encoded
155 - Only character values 0 to 255 are supported in the font file.
156*/
157#ifndef U8G2_WITHOUT_UNICODE
158#define U8G2_WITH_UNICODE
159#endif
160
161
162/*
163 See issue https://github.com/olikraus/u8g2/issues/1561
164 The old behaviour of the StrWidth and UTF8Width functions returned an unbalanced string width, where
165 a small space was added to the left but not to the right of the string in some cases.
166 The new "balanced" procedure will assume the same gap on the left and the right side of the string
167
168 Example: The string width of "C" with font u8g2_font_helvR08_tr was returned as 7.
169 A frame of width 9 would place the C a little bit more to the right (width of that "C" are 6 pixel).
170 If U8G2_BALANCED_STR_WIDTH_CALCULATION is defined, the width of "C" is returned as 8.
171
172 Not defining U8G2_BALANCED_STR_WIDTH_CALCULATION would fall back to the old behavior.
173*/
174#ifndef U8G2_NO_BALANCED_STR_WIDTH_CALCULATION
175#define U8G2_BALANCED_STR_WIDTH_CALCULATION
176#endif
177

208#ifdef U8G2_16BIT
209typedef uint16_t u8g2_uint_t; /* for pixel position only */
210typedef int16_t u8g2_int_t; /* introduced for circle calculation */
211typedef int32_t u8g2_long_t; /* introduced for ellipse calculation */
212#else
213typedef uint8_t u8g2_uint_t; /* for pixel position only */
214typedef int8_t u8g2_int_t; /* introduced for circle calculation */
215typedef int16_t u8g2_long_t; /* introduced for ellipse calculation */
216#endif
217

219typedef struct u8g2_struct u8g2_t;
220typedef struct u8g2_cb_struct u8g2_cb_t;
221
222typedef void (*u8g2_update_dimension_cb)(u8g2_t *u8g2);
223typedef void (*u8g2_update_page_win_cb)(u8g2_t *u8g2);
224typedef void (*u8g2_draw_l90_cb)(u8g2_t *u8g2, u8g2_uint_t x, u8g2_uint_t y, u8g2_uint_t len, uint8_t dir);
225typedef void (*u8g2_draw_ll_hvline_cb)(u8g2_t *u8g2, u8g2_uint_t x, u8g2_uint_t y, u8g2_uint_t len, uint8_t dir);

230/* from ucglib... */
231struct _u8g2_font_info_t
232{
233 /* offset 0 */
234 uint8_t glyph_cnt;
235 uint8_t bbx_mode;
236 uint8_t bits_per_0;
237 uint8_t bits_per_1;
238
239 /* offset 4 */
240 uint8_t bits_per_char_width;
241 uint8_t bits_per_char_height;
242 uint8_t bits_per_char_x;
243 uint8_t bits_per_char_y;
244 uint8_t bits_per_delta_x;
245
246 /* offset 9 */
247 int8_t max_char_width;
248 int8_t max_char_height; /* overall height, NOT ascent. Instead ascent = max_char_height + y_offset */
249 int8_t x_offset;
250 int8_t y_offset;
251
252 /* offset 13 */
253 int8_t ascent_A;
254 int8_t descent_g; /* usually a negative value */
255 int8_t ascent_para;
256 int8_t descent_para;
257
258 /* offset 17 */
259 uint16_t start_pos_upper_A;
260 uint16_t start_pos_lower_a;
261
262 /* offset 21 */
263#ifdef U8G2_WITH_UNICODE
264 uint16_t start_pos_unicode;
265#endif
266};
267typedef struct _u8g2_font_info_t u8g2_font_info_t;
268
269/* from ucglib... */
270struct _u8g2_font_decode_t
271{
272 const uint8_t *decode_ptr; /* pointer to the compressed data */
273
274 u8g2_uint_t target_x;
275 u8g2_uint_t target_y;
276
277 int8_t x; /* local coordinates, (0,0) is upper left */
278 int8_t y;
279 int8_t glyph_width;
280 int8_t glyph_height;
281
282 uint8_t decode_bit_pos; /* bitpos inside a byte of the compressed data */
283 uint8_t is_transparent;
284 uint8_t fg_color;
285 uint8_t bg_color;
286#ifdef U8G2_WITH_FONT_ROTATION
287 uint8_t dir; /* direction */
288#endif
289};
290typedef struct _u8g2_font_decode_t u8g2_font_decode_t;
291
292struct _u8g2_kerning_t
293{
294 uint16_t first_table_cnt;
295 uint16_t second_table_cnt;
296 const uint16_t *first_encoding_table;
297 const uint16_t *index_to_second_table;
298 const uint16_t *second_encoding_table;
299 const uint8_t *kerning_values;
300};
301typedef struct _u8g2_kerning_t u8g2_kerning_t;
302

304struct u8g2_cb_struct
305{
306 u8g2_update_dimension_cb update_dimension;
307 u8g2_update_page_win_cb update_page_win;
308 u8g2_draw_l90_cb draw_l90;
309};

311typedef u8g2_uint_t (*u8g2_font_calc_vref_fnptr)(u8g2_t *u8g2);
312
313
314struct u8g2_struct
315{
316 u8x8_t u8x8;
317 u8g2_draw_ll_hvline_cb ll_hvline; /* low level hvline procedure */
318 const u8g2_cb_t *cb; /* callback drawprocedures, can be replaced for rotation */
319
320 /* the following variables must be assigned during u8g2 setup */
321 uint8_t *tile_buf_ptr; /* ptr to memory area with u8x8.display_info->tile_width * 8 * tile_buf_height bytes */
322 uint8_t tile_buf_height; /* height of the tile memory area in tile rows */
323 uint8_t tile_curr_row; /* current row for picture loop */
324
325 /* dimension of the buffer in pixel */
326 u8g2_uint_t pixel_buf_width; /* equal to tile_buf_width*8 */
327 u8g2_uint_t pixel_buf_height; /* tile_buf_height*8 */
328 u8g2_uint_t pixel_curr_row; /* u8g2.tile_curr_row*8 */
329
330 /* the following variables are set by the update dimension callback */
331 /* this is the clipbox after rotation for the hvline procedures */
332 //u8g2_uint_t buf_x0; /* left corner of the buffer */
333 //u8g2_uint_t buf_x1; /* right corner of the buffer (excluded) */
334 u8g2_uint_t buf_y0;
335 u8g2_uint_t buf_y1;
336
337 /* display dimensions in pixel for the user, calculated in u8g2_update_dimension_common() */
338 u8g2_uint_t width;
339 u8g2_uint_t height;
340
341 /* this is the clip box for the user to check if a specific box has an intersection */
342 /* use u8g2_IsIntersection from u8g2_intersection.c to test against this intersection */
343 /* actually, this window describes the position of the current page */
344 u8g2_uint_t user_x0; /* left corner of the buffer */
345 u8g2_uint_t user_x1; /* right corner of the buffer (excluded) */
346 u8g2_uint_t user_y0; /* upper edge of the buffer */
347 u8g2_uint_t user_y1; /* lower edge of the buffer (excluded) */
348
349#ifdef U8G2_WITH_CLIP_WINDOW_SUPPORT
350 /* clip window */
351 u8g2_uint_t clip_x0; /* left corner of the clip window */
352 u8g2_uint_t clip_x1; /* right corner of the clip window (excluded) */
353 u8g2_uint_t clip_y0; /* upper edge of the clip window */
354 u8g2_uint_t clip_y1; /* lower edge of the clip window (excluded) */
355#endif /* U8G2_WITH_CLIP_WINDOW_SUPPORT */
356
357
358 /* information about the current font */
359 const uint8_t *font; /* current font for all text procedures */
360 // removed: const u8g2_kerning_t *kerning; /* can be NULL */
361 // removed: u8g2_get_kerning_cb get_kerning_cb;
362
363 u8g2_font_calc_vref_fnptr font_calc_vref;
364 u8g2_font_decode_t font_decode; /* new font decode structure */
365 u8g2_font_info_t font_info; /* new font info structure */
366
367#ifdef U8G2_WITH_CLIP_WINDOW_SUPPORT
368 /* 1 of there is an intersection between user_?? and clip_?? box */
369 uint8_t is_page_clip_window_intersection;
370#endif /* U8G2_WITH_CLIP_WINDOW_SUPPORT */
371
372 uint8_t font_height_mode;
373 int8_t font_ref_ascent;
374 int8_t font_ref_descent;
375
376 int8_t glyph_x_offset; /* set by u8g2_GetGlyphWidth as a side effect */
377
378 uint8_t bitmap_transparency; /* black pixels will be treated as transparent (not drawn) */
379
380 uint8_t draw_color; /* 0: clear pixel, 1: set pixel, modified and restored by font procedures */
381 /* draw_color can be used also directly by the user API */
382
383 // the following variable should be renamed to is_buffer_auto_clear
384 uint8_t is_auto_page_clear; /* set to 0 to disable automatic clear of the buffer in firstPage() and nextPage() */
385
386};

1800 all clipping done
